In antwer to yd of 15th cuitt. deare freind not with standing all my endeavoras
I can not pas uitlout roubling you & other freinds I lave been att Brussels
though well 10 dayes before mij surne, a lave been dis afointed by noless then
ƒ 2000 - en pay, so that I am quite out of order for mony, so at p AV. do desire
mee not to redran, what ever they draw on mee so lave endeavoar to finde
mony on you att Rito, butt itt beeng so small a summe noboddy would take
itt att such a uine, so was forted to do itt att diso of yeasterday in my bill
for £100- payable to the ord. of Paulex Rircliel charin valew of Sumself, for
which pray give due sn, a in case att due day you can not comply with the
payment I promise to rembourse you, whilst in the meale while you conld do mee
a hindness to take our resting concernes to yd. silf, & I'll allow you savorabee condid
I should dularge upon the particolars of yd letter, butt I hope you do not saspces
mee of mistenst, or reall, in tegertie with you

mij last to you was on the 21: cuutt. sence recd. yd. of yd. I finde mive of the 1p answered
butt not a word of that of the 7h, which I doubt not butt you lave reeaved also, & the
valew then remitted. I shall exspect what goods I gave orders for, & faile not to send
the nw. red, & E sallow marce, & otha pack whites, for these hen ae most sold
I finde invoyce of a bale of Spanish cloathes abourd sslever warner: as soome as
the bale of fine cloathes is compleated, please to desist in buying of spanish cloathes
till further order, for I thinck them, & the rest of my orders for other goods will
keer the ware touse in good assortment till next Ipring, for trade of or sale beguuis
to decraise already, whilst in the intrim I'ls make n of that time to & rourde
monyes for yd a my acctt
